 Thomas]] (born 1944), head of the United States Environmental Protection Agency, 1985\u20131989\n* [[Leland Evan Thomas]] (1918\u20131942), United States Marine Corps pilot\n* [[Len Thomas]] (1908\u20131943), Australian rules footballer\n* [[Leo Thomas]] (1923\u20132001), American baseball player\n* [[Leon Thomas]] (1937\u20131999), American jazz singer\n* [[Leon Thomas III]] (born 1993), American actor, songwriter and singer\n* [[Leron Thomas]] (born 1979), American jazz trumpeter, composer and vocalist\n* [[LeSean Thomas]] (born 1975), American TV animation producer, director, animator, comic book artist and writer\n* [[Leslie Thomas (disambiguation)|Les and Leslie Thomas (disambiguation)]], multiple people\n** [[Les Thomas (footballer)]] (1906\u20131997), Australian rules footballer for Collingwood\n** [[Les Thomas]], Welsh rugby union and rugby league footballer who played in the 1940s\n*** [[Leslie Thomas (politician)]] (1906\u20131971), British Conservative politician\n*** [[Leslie Thomas]] (1931\u20132014), British author\n*** [[Leslie Thomas (barrister)]] (born 1965), British barrister\n* [[Lewis Thomas (disambiguation)]], multiple people\n** [[Lewis Thomas (bishop)]] (died 1561), Bishop of Shrewsbury\n** [[Lewis Thomas (politician)]] (1832\u20131913), colliery owner and politician in Queensland, Australia\n** [[Lewis Cobden Thomas]] (1865\u20131928), Wales international rugby union footballer\n** [[Lewis Thomas]] (1913\u20131993), American physician, poet, etymologist, essayist, administrator, and educator\n* [[Lillian Thomas]] (born 1949), Canadian politician in Winnipeg\n* [[Lillo Thomas]] (born 1961), American athlete and soul musician\n* [[Lily Thomas]] (1927\u20132019), Indian lawyer\n* [[Lindsay Thomas (disambiguation)]], multiple people\n** [[Lindsay Thomas (politician)]] (born 1943), American politician and businessman\n** [[Lindsay Thomas (actress)]] (1978\u20132010), Canadian stage actress\n* [[Linn Thomas]] (born 1976), American erotic model\n* 